  "body": "Rook could benefit from using `errors.Wrap()` as well as `errors.Wrapf()` so the error formatting is handled by the package. Many projects under the Kubernetes umbrella use it. Also:\r\n\r\n* from a formatting standpoint, the code will be cleaner\r\n* reviews will be more focus since reviewers won't have to explicitly explain on to handle errors and which interface type to use (`%v` versus `+%` for example)\r\n\r\nCurrently, they are around 1414 occurrence of `fmt.Errorf` which should be changed so we need to decide as a group :).\r\nThis means using `\"github.com/pkg/errors\"`.",
